<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf1c31a3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s10249"><num value="10249">§ 10249.</num><heading> Cooperation of other departments and agencies</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each department, agency, and instrumentality of the United States, including any independent agency, may furnish the Negotiator such information as he determines to be necessary to carry out his functions under this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbf1c31a4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/97/425/tIV/s409">Pub. L. 97–425, title IV, § 409</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/100/202/s101/d/tIII">Pub. L. 100–202, § 101(d) [title III]</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1329-104">101 Stat. 1329–104</ref>, 1329–121; <ref href="/us/pl/100/203/tV/s5041">Pub. L. 100–203, title V, § 5041</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1330-247">101 Stat. 1330–247</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
